 Updated on: April 11, 2026

 Copyright ©2026 Oitswilliam Pang. This license is proprietary to this
repository. This license applies to Bunny350/alpha-ea, the derivatives
and its contents.

  Oitswilliam Pang Alpha-stage early access projects are private, members-
only projects that are intended to be previewed and tapped by the
followers of Oitswilliam Pang before their official release. These
projects may be unstable, such as constant revision changes or raw
material changes. Users may not redistribute or sell parts or projects
that are in alpha-EA until its official release.

  - Terms and conditions

  0. Definitions:
  
  Bunny350 is Oitswilliam Pang's GitHub username.
  
  "Alpha-stage early access", sometimes known as "alpha-EA" or
"follower-EA", means a project is in alpha-stage early access. It is
usually internal until all the basics are made and ready to followers
to test it and flag issues prior beta-stage early access or official
release. The original alpha-EA repository is Bunny350/alpha-ea.

  "Beta-stage early access", known as "beta-EA" or just "EA", means a
project is in beta-stage early access. It is public, meaning stalkers
can access these parts and even its source, not just members within OIWP
or the followers. Some projects may just start in beta-EA without
alpha-EA. This will not be broken.

  "Follower-exclusive" means a project Oitswilliam Pang published is
exclusive to the followers of Oitswilliam Pang. They will not be released
to the public, meaning stalkers will not see its models.

  "Reverse engineering" means to re-create the model by-procedure. The
similar procedure applies to vectors or arts as "tracing".

  "Redistribute" means users publish a copy of the project to other
platforms, which can be done by anybody, from creator to stalkers, or
create own copy of the repository or specific project.

  "Members within OIWP" means people whose within (any one of jobs of)
the Oitswilliam Pang group.

  "Followers" means the people who are following the creator of the
project, Oitswilliam Pang, in one, any or all applicable platforms.
These includes the subscribers of Oitswilliam Pang on YouTube.

  "Stalkers" means the people whose never heard of and / or aren't
following or unfollowed (if last) the creator of the project,
Oitswilliam Pang.

  The way the project "move away from alpha-EA" is whether the project
moves to beta-EA or official release, to the public parent repository or
to its own repository.

  1. Permissions

    1.1. Requirements and Obtaining
    Alpha-EA projects can only be obtainable by members within OIWP and
    the followers of Oitswilliam Pang. Stalkers may not access, obtain,
    download, transmit, or even use alpha-EA parts. To access alpha-EA
    projects, you are required to join OITSWILLIAM PANG Discord chat
    server and have filled the member joining form. You must also know
    that unfollowing Oitswilliam Pang in the last platform following or
    leaving OITSWILLIAM PANG Discord chat server (including getting kicked
    or banned) will lose access to such repository per section 1.4.
    Termination.
    
    Note that users joined can only grant a license to access alpha-EA
    projects (do not actually own), unless if such project gets out of
    alpha-EA. Please refer to section 2. Changing license on how the
    project gets out of alpha-EA stage.
    
    Alpha-EA will be broken and will be no more if one of applicable
    Oitswilliam Pang's platform has reached over 10,000 followers.
    All follower-exclusive models will become available to non-
    followers if one of applicable Oitswilliam Pang's platform has
    reached over 15,000 followers. Oitswilliam Pang reserves the
    final decision on whether the status stay, the exclusivity can be
    broken or not.

    1.2. Sharing
    Parts of, or the entire project in alpha-EA may not be shared,
    transmitted, redistributed or sold to outsiders, including but not
    limited to for stalkers, public archival or excuses that allow the
    parts to be shown public. Anyone whose shared or attempting to share
    to outsiders, including redistributing to other platforms, or reverse
    engineering, will result in losing access to such repository per
    section 1.4. Termination, and may lead to copyright / works
    infringement.
    Anyone, however, is allowed to share photos and videos of projects
    that are in alpha-EA, and while at it tag Oitswilliam
    @williampang.3363 on Facebook, @william86745 on Instagram and / or
    @oitswilliam on YouTube.

    1.3. Modifications
    Modifications are condemned if they do not have the following
    documents:
    - For CAD 3D models, STEP or f3d,
    - For vectors, ai or svg,
    - For renders, blend,
    - Any software that does not have any source code, which is
    impossible.
    Modifications made for projects in alpha-EA may not be published
    publicly and must wait until when the project goes away from such
    stage. If the published model is a model of a project inside alpha-EA
    that is tampered with, they will lose access to such repository per
    section 1.4. Termination. You may not use these projects to create
    weapons.

    1.4 Termination
    Anyone whose violate alpha-EA licensing may result in losing access
    to the repository. The following violations which will result in
    access losing without any warning: Leaving / getting kicked or banned
    in OITSWILLIAM PANG Discord chat server, unfollowing Oitswilliam Pang
    in the last platform following, tampering the documents, publishing
    the models from the project in alpha-EA that has been tampered with,
    patent troll, using bot to scrap such repository's or projects'
    information, and attempting to challenge with the terms of conditions
    of the license or the entire license. Anyone will be warned once
    before termination if they have caught publishing models that aren't
    tampered, but will still result in termination if they refuse
    receiving warnings in any way (for example, blocking Oitswilliam from
    sending to) or repeated / chaining offense.
    Oitswilliam Pang will have the final decision on whether to warn the
    member or terminate their access, with no explicitly said ban
    duration.
    
    If you have lost access to alpha-EA repository due to termination,
    you are ordered to do nothing else, and then remove alpha-EA
    repository from your devices permanently. This does not apply to
    parts that became physical in real life, in which can be kept.

  2. Changing license
  Oitswilliam Pang will be required to change the project's licensing
away from alpha-EA license when the project decides to go outside
alpha-EA. This also means that, if the project is in beta-EA, or released
officially, users are allowed to own versions of the project that are in
alpha-EA stage.

Anyone else are not allowed to change the license or licensing terms of
projects in alpha-EA or they will lose access for tampering the documents
per section 1.4. Termination.

  3. Commercial and Patents
  Since these projects are put in alpha-EA, and is not allowed to have
parts published outside, commercial purposes, including selling, or
mass-producing these parts are not allowed and may result in losing
access per section 1.4. Termination. Anyone whose isn't Oitswilliam Pang
may not make patents from projects created by Oitswilliam Pang. Anyone
whose having the goal of scraping money out of Oitswilliam's projects,
also known as patent trolling, will result in losing access per section
1.4. Termination.

  4. Warranty
  These materials, documents and models are PROVIDED "AS-IS" WITHOUT
  WARRANTY.

  5. Liability
  Anyone using the project is liable to themselves. Use at own risk.

  - The end of terms and conditions

  - Questions
  
  1. Can I share materials that contain projects in alpha-EA?
    For the exact models (STL, 3MF or source), no, that needs the models
    getting out of alpha-EA first, but as in photos or videos, yes,
    you can.
    
  2. Can I modify models that are in alpha-stage early access?
    It is generally condemned from modifying alpha-EA models as they will
    be constantly changed. So unless you really want to make your own
    unique mod due to current model's issues, you may wait for it to get
    out of alpha-EA first. Also, the mod must not include the models
    based from the project that is in alpha-EA.
    
  3. Why am I required joining OITSWILLIAM PANG Discord server prior
  opt-in?
    This is because we will be making updates exclusively through such
    Discord chat server. And this heavily relies on that, like for
    example you will lose access to such repository if you for whatever
    reason left this chat server or got kicked or banned in this chat
    server.

  4. Why are non-followers not allowed to access such repository?
    This is because we don't want to spoil our plans, whatever that
    means, beside this, everyone has selections, but when we decide to
    make a fresh new project, we like to gather people just to show it.
    And yes, if any (previous) followers unfollowed Oitswilliam on the
    last platform they are following, they will lose access to such
    repository, among other things.
    
  5. Is generative AI or robots with internet access allowed to use this
      repository?
    No, they can get out. Only real humans can access and surf around
    this repository. Thank you for understanding.
  
  6. Can I sell parts of projects that are in alpha-EA?
    In short answer, no, in long answer, it is not allowed due to it
    being able to be distributed to stalkers (people who did not yet
    following Oitswilliam), as such it might lead sellers be punished
    under section 1.2. Sharing. Not just this, we are generally not ready
    for this yet, so, logically, tell people to have their own printer if
    they want the parts (when they are released).

  7. Do users really own alpha-EA projects?
    NO, unless if the project is out of such stage.
    According to alpha-EA licensing, users do not own Oitswilliam's
    projects that are in alpha-EA unless if they are out of such stage.
    Users whose intent is to violate alpha-EA licensing shall require
    removal of the repository in their device forever.
    Follower-exclusive projects may not see itself be ownable by the
    people within the forseeable future.
